      <texts>
        <txt c="X" s="1" w="750" y="75" x="20">It is important to use correct lifting techniques to avoid injuries to back and shoulders. If the object is very heavy and/or warm, two persons have to carry the object between them. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Preparations:  </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2" x="40">Stand as close as possible in front of what you are going to lift. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Stand on a steady base. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Stand with the legs a little apart, or one leg slightly in front of the other. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Stand in the same direction as you are going to lift. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Evaluate how heavy the lift will be. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Bend your knees, bend your upper body forward. Hold your back straight. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Take a good and steady grip on what to lift </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="1" y="400" x="20">The lift: </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2" x="40">Straighten your ankles, knees and hips. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Hold the back straight. </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">Hold the object close to you body.  </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">
        </txt>
        <txt c="X" s="2">
        </txt>
      </texts>
